        <h2>Guidelines for Vendors</h2>
        <p>Welcome to the Vendor Guidelines section. Please follow the guidelines below to ensure smooth collaboration and successful participation in tenders:</p>
        
        <h3>1. Registration and Profile Management</h3>
        <p>Ensure that all information provided during registration is accurate and up-to-date. Regularly review and update your profile to reflect any changes in your business.</p>

        <h3>2. Tender Submission</h3>
        <p>Submit your tenders before the deadline. Late submissions will not be considered. Ensure all required documents are included and properly filled out.</p>

        <h3>3. Compliance with Regulations</h3>
        <p>Adhere to all relevant laws and regulations related to the procurement process. Failure to comply may result in disqualification from future tenders.</p>

        <h3>4. Communication</h3>
        <p>Maintain clear and professional communication with the buyers. Respond to queries promptly and provide any additional information requested.</p>

        <h3>5. Quality and Delivery</h3>
        <p>Ensure that the products or services delivered meet the agreed specifications and quality standards. Timely delivery is crucial for successful transactions.</p>

        <h3>6. Feedback and Improvement</h3>
        <p>Be open to feedback and use it constructively to improve your services. Regularly review feedback provided by buyers to enhance your performance.</p>
